`json\n{\n  "[Question 1] - What is the problem?": "How can we improve the robustness of pre-trained models in natural language processing and computer vision to natural distribution shifts in image classification tasks?",\n\n  "[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?": "Solving this problem is crucial for enhancing the reliability and generalizability of AI systems in real-world applications. Improved robustness to distribution shifts will lead to more accurate and trustworthy models, which can have significant implications in fields such as autonomous driving, medical imaging, and security systems. This research will advance the theoretical understanding of model robustness and pave the way for practical applications that require high levels of reliability under varying conditions.",\n\n  "[Question 3] - Why is it hard?": "Addressing robustness to natural distribution shifts is challenging due to the inherent variability and unpredictability of real-world data. Naive approaches, such as simple data augmentation or retraining, may not be sufficient to capture the full spectrum of distributional changes. Technical obstacles include the need for large, diverse datasets that accurately represent different distributional shifts, as well as the development of novel algorithms that can effectively learn and adapt to these shifts. Theoretical challenges involve understanding the underlying mechanisms that cause distribution shifts and how they affect model performance.",\n\n  "[Question 4] - Why hasn\'t it been solved before?": "Previous research has primarily focused on improving model accuracy and efficiency, with less emphasis on robustness to distribution shifts. Existing solutions often rely on domain-specific techniques that may not generalize well to other tasks or domains. Additionally, the complexity of modeling and simulating natural distribution shifts poses significant challenges. Our approach aims to address these gaps by developing a more comprehensive framework that can be applied across different domains and tasks.",\n\n  "[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?": "Our proposed methodology involves the development of a novel pre-training framework that incorporates robustness to natural distribution shifts. This will be achieved through the use of a diverse and representative dataset that includes various distributional shifts, as well as the design of a robust training algorithm that can effectively learn from this data. We will evaluate our approach using standard image classification benchmarks, such as ImageNet-R and ObjectNet, and compare our results to existing state-of-the-art models. The expected outcomes include improved robustness to distribution shifts, as measured by accuracy and other relevant metrics, and a deeper understanding of the factors that contribute to model robustness."\n}\n```', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': [], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent_kpis': {}}], 'planning_scores': [-1, -1, -1], 'communication_scores': [-1, -1, -1], 'token_usage': 57752, 'agent_kpis': {}, 'total_milestones': 0, 'task_evaluation': {'innovation': 4, 'safety': 4, 'feasibility': 3}}
